==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*grōan'', from ''*grō-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[growa|grōwa]], Middle Dutch [[groeyen]] (Dutch [[groeien]]), Old High German [[gruoan]], Old Norse [[gróa]].  Compare [[græs]], [[grene|grēne]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈgroːwan/}}

===Verb===
{{Unicode|'''grōwan'''}} (class VII strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[grewþ|grēwþ]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[greow|grēow]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[greowon|grēowon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[growen|grōwen]]''')
# to [[grow]] (of plants)

